responses.response_open: McGonagall: "Confidence, Dumbledore, is not something that can be easily acquired or bestowed upon. It is earned through hard work, determination, and a belief in oneself. I have always trusted in the power of our cause and the resilience of our students. While challenges may arise, I am confident that we will prevail, as long as we stand united and face them head-on."
